[
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 0.49
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES GRIME: Today, we're going\nto talk about one of the",
        "start": 0.49,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "questions that we get sent in a\nlot at Numberphile, and the",
        "start": 2.19,
        "duration": 4.37
    },
    {
        "text": "question is-- well, Brady,\nwhat's the question?",
        "start": 6.56,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: The question is,\nwhy does 0 factorial equal 1?",
        "start": 9.56,
        "duration": 4.98
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES GRIME: Right.",
        "start": 14.54,
        "duration": 0.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Why does 0 factorial equal 1?",
        "start": 14.88,
        "duration": 2.33
    },
    {
        "text": "So let's start off with a\nquick recap of what a",
        "start": 17.21,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "factorial is.",
        "start": 19.9,
        "duration": 1.05
    },
    {
        "text": "For our whole number, let's\npick a number n--",
        "start": 20.95,
        "duration": 2.702
    },
    {
        "text": "n factorial, which is written\nlike that. n with an",
        "start": 23.652,
        "duration": 2.648
    },
    {
        "text": "exclamation mark.",
        "start": 26.3,
        "duration": 1.82
    },
    {
        "text": "This is equal to.",
        "start": 28.12,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "You multiply all the\nwhole numbers less",
        "start": 29.67,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "than or equal to n.",
        "start": 32.34,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "It's n multiplied by n minus\n1 multiplied by n minus 2",
        "start": 34.33,
        "duration": 5.88
    },
    {
        "text": "multiplied by--",
        "start": 40.21,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and you keep going down,\nand you'll go down to 3",
        "start": 41.37,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "times 2 times 1.",
        "start": 43.78,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "Quick example.",
        "start": 45.97,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's do 5 factorial.",
        "start": 46.97,
        "duration": 1.26
    },
    {
        "text": "5 times 4 times 3\ntimes 2 times 1.",
        "start": 48.23,
        "duration": 4.43
    },
    {
        "text": "And you do that.",
        "start": 52.66,
        "duration": 0.71
    },
    {
        "text": "It's 120.",
        "start": 53.37,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "OK.",
        "start": 54.89,
        "duration": 0.56
    },
    {
        "text": "The question we've been asked\nis what is 0 factorial.",
        "start": 55.45,
        "duration": 2.6
    },
    {
        "text": "So the way you can answer this--\none of the ways you can",
        "start": 58.05,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "answer this is to complete\nthe pattern.",
        "start": 60.66,
        "duration": 2.52
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's complete the pattern.",
        "start": 63.18,
        "duration": 1.02
    },
    {
        "text": "This pattern in particular,\n4 factorial, is equal to 5",
        "start": 64.2,
        "duration": 4.11
    },
    {
        "text": "factorial divided by 5.",
        "start": 68.31,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "If you can see that, if I take 5\nfactorial here and divide by",
        "start": 70.44,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "5, that means I can knock\noff that 5, and you",
        "start": 74.28,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "end up with 4 factorial.",
        "start": 77.79,
        "duration": 2.04
    },
    {
        "text": "So 5 factorial divided\nby 5, or 120 divided",
        "start": 79.83,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "by 5, that's 24.",
        "start": 83.29,
        "duration": 2.13
    },
    {
        "text": "That's 4 factorial.",
        "start": 85.42,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "3 factorial is going to be\n4 factorial divided by 4.",
        "start": 86.67,
        "duration": 4.7
    },
    {
        "text": "That's 24 divided by 4.",
        "start": 91.37,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "That's 6.",
        "start": 94.81,
        "duration": 0.98
    },
    {
        "text": "That's the answer\nto 3 factorial.",
        "start": 95.79,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "2 factorial, 3 factorial divided\nby 3, 6, which we've",
        "start": 97.27,
        "duration": 3.91
    },
    {
        "text": "just worked out, divided\nby 3, equals 2.",
        "start": 101.18,
        "duration": 3.55
    },
    {
        "text": "1 factorial.",
        "start": 104.73,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "Do it again.",
        "start": 106.8,
        "duration": 1.09
    },
    {
        "text": "It's 2 factorial divided by 2.",
        "start": 107.89,
        "duration": 3.39
    },
    {
        "text": "2 factorial is 2 divided by 2.",
        "start": 111.28,
        "duration": 2.77
    },
    {
        "text": "We've got 2 divided by 2.",
        "start": 114.05,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "That's equal to 1.",
        "start": 116.13,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "Now this is where it's\ngetting exciting.",
        "start": 117.78,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you feel the anticipation?",
        "start": 119.15,
        "duration": 1.73
    },
    {
        "text": "So 0 factorial.",
        "start": 120.88,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "We're going to complete\nthe pattern.",
        "start": 122.48,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "0 factorial is 1 factorial\ndivided by 1.",
        "start": 124.88,
        "duration": 6.46
    },
    {
        "text": "1 factorial is 1.",
        "start": 131.34,
        "duration": 2.38
    },
    {
        "text": "It's 1 divided by 1, and\nthat is equal to 1.",
        "start": 133.72,
        "duration": 4.35
    },
    {
        "text": "So 0 factorial is equal to 1.",
        "start": 138.07,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "You complete the pattern.",
        "start": 141.43,
        "duration": 0.92
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Who says the\npattern has to be complete?",
        "start": 142.35,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": "Where's that rule come from?",
        "start": 144.54,
        "duration": 2.45
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES GRIME: I guess it doesn't\nnecessarily have to be",
        "start": 146.99,
        "duration": 3.98
    },
    {
        "text": "a pattern that completes.",
        "start": 150.97,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "It is a pattern that\ncompetes, though.",
        "start": 151.82,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "Let me try another way\nto explain it.",
        "start": 153.35,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Let me continue\nthe pattern first.",
        "start": 156.29,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "Does that mean negative 1\nfactorial would be next in",
        "start": 158.1,
        "duration": 3.25
    },
    {
        "text": "that sequence?",
        "start": 161.35,
        "duration": 1.25
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES GRIME: Let's\nsee what happens.",
        "start": 162.6,
        "duration": 0.765
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm not sure what's\ngoing to happen.",
        "start": 163.365,
        "duration": 1.175
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's try.",
        "start": 164.54,
        "duration": 0.81
    },
    {
        "text": "Minus 1 factorial.",
        "start": 165.35,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "So what shall I get?",
        "start": 167.46,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": "0 factorial divided by 0.",
        "start": 168.22,
        "duration": 3.81
    },
    {
        "text": "1 divided by 0.",
        "start": 172.03,
        "duration": 1.905
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: Oh, divided by 0.",
        "start": 173.935,
        "duration": 2.275
    },
    {
        "text": "JAMES GRIME: You've broken\nmaths, Brady.",
        "start": 176.21,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Stop that.",
        "start": 177.51,
        "duration": 0.76
    },
    {
        "text": "Another way to explain what\n0 factorial might be.",
        "start": 178.27,
        "duration": 4.34
    },
    {
        "text": "n factorial is the number\nof ways you",
        "start": 182.61,
        "duration": 2.085
    },
    {
        "text": "can arrange n objects.",
        "start": 184.695,
        "duration": 2.395
    },
    {
        "text": "Let me just try to show\nyou what I mean.",
        "start": 187.09,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's get some objects.",
        "start": 188.59,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "I'll get the wallet out.",
        "start": 189.54,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "I'll get some coins out.",
        "start": 191.41,
        "duration": 2.86
    },
    {
        "text": "See?",
        "start": 194.27,
        "duration": 0.47
    },
    {
        "text": "Who says mathematicians don't\nmake a lot of money?",
        "start": 194.74,
        "duration": 2.06
    },
    {
        "text": "There's literally 50p here.",
        "start": 196.8,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's pick a silver\none and a 5p one.",
        "start": 200.22,
        "duration": 4.19
    },
    {
        "text": "Three objects here, and how many\nways are there to arrange",
        "start": 204.41,
        "duration": 4.35
    },
    {
        "text": "three objects?",
        "start": 208.76,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "There's six ways to do it.",
        "start": 209.94,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "It's 3 factorial.",
        "start": 211.14,
        "duration": 1.1
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's just check them.",
        "start": 212.24,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "That's one, that's two, or we\ncould have this one here--",
        "start": 213.36,
        "duration": 5.26
    },
    {
        "text": "that's three, that's four.",
        "start": 218.62,
        "duration": 3.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Or we could have--",
        "start": 222.18,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "I think it was that one we\ndidn't have at the front.",
        "start": 224.02,
        "duration": 1.64
    },
    {
        "text": "So that would be five and six.",
        "start": 225.66,
        "duration": 3.715
    },
    {
        "text": "If we take one away, we\nhave now two objects.",
        "start": 229.375,
        "duration": 4.295
    },
    {
        "text": "How many ways are there to\narrange two objects?",
        "start": 233.67,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "That's one, that's two.",
        "start": 235.29,
        "duration": 3.75
    },
    {
        "text": "Take one away.",
        "start": 239.04,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "How many ways are there\nto arrange one object?",
        "start": 240.79,
        "duration": 3.19
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 243.98,
        "duration": 0.43
    },
    {
        "text": "There's one way to do it.",
        "start": 244.41,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "One way to arrange one object.",
        "start": 246.07,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "Now we're going to take\nthe last coin away.",
        "start": 247.46,
        "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
        "text": "This is where it gets a\nlittle philosophical.",
        "start": 250.46,
        "duration": 3.59
    },
    {
        "text": "We have zero objects.",
        "start": 254.05,
        "duration": 2.279
    },
    {
        "text": "How many ways are there to\narrange zero objects?",
        "start": 256.329,
        "duration": 3.51
    },
    {
        "text": "There's one way to do it.",
        "start": 259.839,
        "duration": 2.291
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 262.13,
        "duration": 1.084
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you want to see\nme do it again?",
        "start": 263.214,
        "duration": 2.161
    },
    {
        "text": "There it is.",
        "start": 265.375,
        "duration": 2.625
    },
    {
        "text": "Slightly philosophical, but\nwe say there is one way to",
        "start": 268.0,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "arrange zero objects.",
        "start": 271.68,
        "duration": 1.41
    },
    {
        "text": "So again, the pattern holds.",
        "start": 273.09,
        "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
        "text": "0 factorial equals 1.",
        "start": 274.72,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "Just to continue the idea just a\nlittle bit further, if we're",
        "start": 278.08,
        "duration": 3.86
    },
    {
        "text": "talking about factorials, let's\ntry and graph them.",
        "start": 281.94,
        "duration": 3.15
    },
    {
        "text": "So let's say let's have one,\ntwo, three, four, five.",
        "start": 285.09,
        "duration": 4.14
    },
    {
        "text": "1 factorial is 1, so\nif you call that 1.",
        "start": 289.23,
        "duration": 3.87
    },
    {
        "text": "2 factorial is 2, so somewhere\nabout here.",
        "start": 293.1,
        "duration": 3.95
    },
    {
        "text": "3 factorial is 6.",
        "start": 297.05,
        "duration": 2.682
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't know.",
        "start": 299.732,
        "duration": 0.758
    },
    {
        "text": "Somewhere like this.",
        "start": 300.49,
        "duration": 1.27
    },
    {
        "text": "4 factorial is 24, so that's\ngoing to be actually quite",
        "start": 301.76,
        "duration": 5.11
    },
    {
        "text": "high up here.",
        "start": 306.87,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "And then 5 factorial is\ngoing quite high.",
        "start": 308.54,
        "duration": 2.21
    },
    {
        "text": "If we join these together,\nI've also said that 0",
        "start": 310.75,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "factorial is 1, so I reckon\nthis is the graph.",
        "start": 313.78,
        "duration": 4.81
    },
    {
        "text": "So in theory, we should be\nable to get values for in",
        "start": 318.59,
        "duration": 4.22
    },
    {
        "text": "between, like, say, the\nnumber 1 and 1/2.",
        "start": 322.81,
        "duration": 3.73
    },
    {
        "text": "1 and 1/2 factorial.",
        "start": 326.54,
        "duration": 0.865
    },
    {
        "text": "What is 1 and 1/2 factorial?",
        "start": 327.405,
        "duration": 1.745
    },
    {
        "text": "So mathematicians\nhave done that.",
        "start": 329.15,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "They generalize the idea.",
        "start": 330.49,
        "duration": 1.87
    },
    {
        "text": "And there is the idea of\n1 and 1/2 factorial.",
        "start": 332.36,
        "duration": 3.97
    },
    {
        "text": "We call it gamma.",
        "start": 336.33,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "That's the Greek letter gamma.",
        "start": 338.75,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "We call it gamma of.",
        "start": 340.61,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "And the way we write it--",
        "start": 342.32,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "actually, now this is getting\na bit more sophisticated.",
        "start": 344.4,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "We say gamma of n is equal to\nthe integral between 0 and",
        "start": 346.81,
        "duration": 4.73
    },
    {
        "text": "infinity of--",
        "start": 351.54,
        "duration": 2.62
    },
    {
        "text": "let's pick something--",
        "start": 354.16,
        "duration": 0.95
    },
    {
        "text": "t to the power n minus 1,\nmultiplied by e to the power",
        "start": 355.11,
        "duration": 6.32
    },
    {
        "text": "minus n dn.",
        "start": 361.43,
        "duration": 4.46
    },
    {
        "text": "Some people won't be\nfamiliar with that.",
        "start": 365.89,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Some of you will be familiar\nwith that.",
        "start": 367.38,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Some of you won't be.",
        "start": 369.33,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": "It's a much more complicated\nmathematical idea, but this",
        "start": 370.34,
        "duration": 4.49
    },
    {
        "text": "would agree with\nthe factorials.",
        "start": 374.83,
        "duration": 3.26
    },
    {
        "text": "But it gives you in between\nvalues as well.",
        "start": 378.09,
        "duration": 2.67
    },
    {
        "text": "It plots this line.",
        "start": 380.76,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "There is something\nI do need to say.",
        "start": 382.86,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "It's slightly unexpected, but if\nwe take a value for a whole",
        "start": 384.85,
        "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
        "text": "number, gamma of n, and n is\nwhole, this actually gives you",
        "start": 391.01,
        "duration": 4.17
    },
    {
        "text": "n minus 1 factorial, so\nbe careful of that.",
        "start": 395.18,
        "duration": 3.79
    },
    {
        "text": "That might catch you out.",
        "start": 398.97,
        "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
        "text": "Bit of a pain, that.",
        "start": 400.6,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "So what's the point of having a\nfunction that will give you",
        "start": 402.06,
        "duration": 3.67
    },
    {
        "text": "factorials in between whole\nnumbers when you can't arrange",
        "start": 405.73,
        "duration": 4.81
    },
    {
        "text": "1 and 1/2 objects?",
        "start": 410.54,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's a generalization, and\nit turns out to be quite",
        "start": 412.07,
        "duration": 3.91
    },
    {
        "text": "useful in many things.",
        "start": 415.98,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Particularly, I'm thinking\nof probability.",
        "start": 417.3,
        "duration": 2.92
    },
    {
        "text": "You can use them in formulas\nthat you find in probability",
        "start": 420.22,
        "duration": 5.47
    },
    {
        "text": "where you're thinking about\ncontinuous time instead of",
        "start": 425.69,
        "duration": 2.99
    },
    {
        "text": "just arranging objects in\ndiscreet probability.",
        "start": 428.68,
        "duration": 3.8
    },
    {
        "text": "You're now starting to think\nabout continuous events.",
        "start": 432.48,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Time is the best example.",
        "start": 435.42,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Then you start to generalize the\nideas, and therefore you",
        "start": 437.74,
        "duration": 3.48
    },
    {
        "text": "need a generalized factorial.",
        "start": 441.22,
        "duration": 2.19
    },
    {
        "text": " ",
        "start": 443.41,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "BRADY HARAN: 9, 6, and 3.",
        "start": 446.14,
        "duration": 7.98
    },
    {
        "text": "20.",
        "start": 454.12,
        "duration": 0.53
    },
    {
        "text": "44.",
        "start": 454.65,
        "duration": 1.55
    }
]